1
00:00:06,890 --> 00:00:09,400
I can't meet them then. I'm in court.
我那会儿不能见他们.我要出庭.

2
00:00:09,642 --> 00:00:10,900
You're in court the next day.
你在那之后第二天才出庭.

3
00:00:11,061 --> 00:00:11,400
Right. 
是的.

4
00:00:11,802 --> 00:00:13,300
But I'm also in court on Wednesday.
但我周三也要出庭.

5
00:00:13,792 --> 00:00:15,400
The next day is Wednesday.
第二天就是周三.

6
00:00:16,236 --> 00:00:19,800
Trish, we just started and we're already out of sync.
Trish,我们才刚开始就已经节奏不同了.

7
00:00:19,922 --> 00:00:21,600
I cannot have all these meetings.
我不能参加所有会议.

8
00:00:21,741 --> 00:00:23,300
There aren't enough hours in the day.
白天没那么多时间.

9
00:00:23,531 --> 00:00:24,700
With all due respect, 
恕我直言,

10
00:00:24,894 --> 00:00:26,500
you don't write things down in the calendar.
你不把事情写在日程表上.

11
00:00:26,591 --> 00:00:28,300
So I don't know how full your schedule is,
所以我不知道你的安排究竟有多满,

12
00:00:28,415 --> 00:00:31,200
which is why we still have these little meetings.
这就是我们还会有这些小会的原因.

13
00:00:31,950 --> 00:00:34,800
Can we agree that the day after Wednesday is Thursday?
我们是否能一致同意周三之后是周四呢?

14
00:00:37,073 --> 00:00:39,500
That's a joke, Trish. A little joke.
开个玩笑,Trish.一个小玩笑.

15
00:00:39,969 --> 00:00:41,500
May we start from the beginning?
我们可以从头开始吗?

16
00:00:41,951 --> 00:00:43,000
By all means.
当然可以.

17
00:00:43,308 --> 00:00:46,900
The Credit Card Association would like to meet with you on Tuesday morning.
信用卡协会想在周二上午见你.

18
00:00:47,405 --> 00:00:49,400
Fine. I can do it in the morning.
好的.可以在早上进行.

19
00:00:49,574 --> 00:00:51,000
Afterwards, I'm in court.
然后我要出庭.

20
00:00:51,247 --> 00:00:52,200
Fine. Which case?
好的.哪个案子?

21
00:00:52,375 --> 00:00:53,800
People vs Kenton.
公众对Kenton.

22
00:00:53,941 --> 00:00:56,100
That case doesn't start until next week!
这案子要到下周才开始.

23
00:00:56,226 --> 00:00:57,700
We're talking about next week!
我们谈的就是下周的安排!

24
00:00:57,863 --> 00:00:58,900
We're talking about this week!
我们谈的是本周的安排!

25
00:00:59,226 --> 00:01:02,100
Trish, I said, "Let's talk about next week."
Trish,我说了,"让我们谈下周的安排."

26
00:01:02,686 --> 00:01:03,900
You said it on Friday.
你是在上周五说的.

27
00:01:04,162 --> 00:01:07,500
Last week, "next week" means " this week" this week.
上周说的"下周"到这周就变成"这周"了.

28
00:01:10,021 --> 00:01:11,800
You're going to make a very good attorney.
你会成为一名出色的律师.

